@page "/hello-world"
@attribute [Authorize]

<PageTitle>Hello World - Whiskers</PageTitle>

@* Example module page — a thin route wrapper (the standard DI-safe pattern). ModuleGuard renders the
   interactive HelloWorldView only when the hello-world module is enabled (Features:hello-world:Enabled=true);
   otherwise it shows a clean "module disabled" notice. Because the view — which injects IHelloWorldGreeter —
   is only instantiated when enabled, a disabled module never triggers a missing-service DI error. *@
<ModuleGuard ModuleId="hello-world">
    <HelloWorldView />
</ModuleGuard>
